        <!-- The slideshow -->
        <div id="slideshow" class="carousel-inner ">
          <div class="carousel-item active">

            <div class="carousel-textbox">

              <h2>3D Model Viewers</h2>

              <p>Many sections of this website employ WebGL technologies
                 to present interactive 3D models directly through your browser.

                Take a look at the example model on this page, drag and scroll
                on the interactive viewer to inspect the bell of a fishing ship
                grounded near the lighthouse museum in Fraserburgh.</p>

            </div>

            <div class="modelbox" id="bell">

            </div>

          </div>
          <div class="carousel-item">
            <div class="carousel-textbox">

              <h2>Virtual Town</h2>

              <p>The virtual town section of this website allows you to view
                buildings of cultural importance through a unique perspective
                within a 3D virtual environment.

                You can view information about the buildings of importance
                within the virtual town, providing an immersive learning experience. </p>

            </div>

            <div id="vrimage" class="image">

            </div>

          </div>
          <div class="carousel-item">
            <div class="carousel-textbox">

              <h2>360 Gallery</h2>

              <p>VCheck out the 360 Gallery to view 360 panoramas of locations of
              cultural importance.</p>

            </div>

            <div id="galleryimage" class="image">

            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Left and right controls -->
        <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#demo" data-slide="prev">
          <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon"></span>
        </a>
        <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#demo" data-slide="next">
          <span class="carousel-control-next-icon"></span>
